out of business, but it still can't do this.

1197
01:33:25,331 --> 01:33:26,628
All right.

1198
01:33:32,204 --> 01:33:35,071
You understand all this. You go to MIT.

1199
01:33:35,441 --> 01:33:36,840
Smart boy.

1200
01:33:38,310 --> 01:33:40,244
My name is Cole Williams.

1201
01:33:40,846 --> 01:33:44,111
And if I ever see you in this town again,

1202
01:33:44,884 --> 01:33:48,285
I will break your cheek bone
with a small hammer,

1203
01:33:49,522 --> 01:33:51,513
and then I will kill you.

1204
01:33:56,195 --> 01:33:59,756
Please. Please just take the money.

1205
01:34:01,000 --> 01:34:02,524
You can take it.

1206
01:34:05,237 --> 01:34:06,568
Tell me,

1207
01:34:07,139 --> 01:34:11,872
how's good old Professor Rosa doing, huh?

1208
01:34:13,546 --> 01:34:18,142
Oh, yeah. Me and Micky, we go way back.

1209
01:34:19,251 --> 01:34:22,243
I spent years, chased him all over this town.

1210
01:34:22,688 --> 01:34:27,648
Giving him beat downs left and right,
only to find him at the tables a week later.

1211
01:34:27,760 --> 01:34:29,728
He was very persistent.

1212
01:34:30,629 --> 01:34:33,928
And then, one September night,

1213
01:34:34,433 --> 01:34:37,334
when I was in Barstow
at my father's funeral,

1214
01:34:38,204 --> 01:34:41,640
my casino was taken for seven figures.

1215
01:34:41,741 --> 01:34:43,072
Can you imagine that?

1216
01:34:43,175 --> 01:34:46,406
The most ever taken by a single counter
in one night.

1217
01:34:46,512 --> 01:34:51,108
'Course I was, naturally,
unceremoniously fired.

1218
01:34:53,819 --> 01:34:55,582
Funny thing, though.

1219
01:34:55,988 --> 01:34:58,513
I never saw Micky Rosa after that.

1220
01:34:59,692 --> 01:35:00,818
Never.

1221
01:36:27,546 --> 01:36:29,673
<i>Cauchy was the first
to make a rigorous study</i>

1222
01:36:29,782 --> 01:36:33,809
of the conditions for convergence
of an infinite series.

1223
01:36:33,919 --> 01:36:36,217
And was concerned with developing

1224
01:36:36,322 --> 01:36:41,191
the basic theorems of the calculus
as rigorously as possible.

1225
01:36:42,595 --> 01:36:44,028
Any questions?

1226
01:36:44,430 --> 01:36:46,557
No? All right, moving on.

1227
01:36:47,600 --> 01:36:51,593
Isn't it true Cauchy stole from his students?

1228
01:36:56,508 --> 01:37:00,376
Yes, I heard that.
What's your theory on that?

1229
01:37:01,413 --> 01:37:05,941
They say he used his students
for their brilliance,

1230
01:37:07,086 --> 01:37:11,318
then discredited them
and stole their equations,

1231
01:37:13,392 --> 01:37:15,257
stole their hard work.

1232
01:37:17,963 --> 01:37:20,659
Well, that wouldn't be the first time
a teacher was accused of that.

1233
01:37:20,766 --> 01:37:25,465
I think what he's referring to
is Vladimir Stupnitsky, yes?

1234
01:37:25,571 --> 01:37:28,506
He was a student of Cauchy's
who accused Cauchy

1235
01:37:28,607 --> 01:37:31,940
of stealing his four-volume text
on this analysis

1236
01:37:32,044 --> 01:37:34,512
and publishing it under a pseudonym.

1237
01:37:36,348 --> 01:37:38,009
Of course, nobody knows
what really went down there.

1238
01:37:38,117 --> 01:37:42,110
They never did prove it, and without
the proof, it's a little like it never happened.

1239
01:37:42,221 --> 01:37:44,246
And, you know, it's a real shame,

1240
01:37:44,356 --> 01:37:48,554
because if Stupnitsky had just realized
that he shouldn't have crossed Cauchy,

1241
01:37:48,661 --> 01:37:50,390
this was the dispute,

1242
01:37:51,430 --> 01:37:57,426
if he'd been able to get beyond some
of the personal mistakes that were made,

1243
01:37:57,970 --> 01:38:01,201
I have no doubt that Cauchy
would have worked with him again,

1244
01:38:01,307 --> 01:38:04,333
and they could have
done great things together.

1245
01:38:04,743 --> 01:38:08,804
But, as history shows us,
some students never learn.

1246
01:38:10,516 --> 01:38:12,177
You should get that eye looked at.

1247
01:38:49,388 --> 01:38:50,787
