01:42:10,789 --> 01:42:15,817
Yeah, I think I probably would have
blown off the 2.09 Competition, too.

1285
01:42:19,364 --> 01:42:20,729
So we cool?

1286
01:42:22,367 --> 01:42:23,959
Yeah, we're cool.

1287
01:42:24,469 --> 01:42:27,165
But you better believe that
you're gonna make this up to me, big time.

1288
01:42:27,272 --> 01:42:28,534
All right.

1289
01:42:29,841 --> 01:42:31,968
So, what are you gonna do now?

1290
01:43:22,761 --> 01:43:24,592
What do you want, Ben?
This is an alumni dinner.

1291
01:43:24,696 --> 01:43:27,062
You need a diploma
to come to one of these.

1292
01:43:27,165 --> 01:43:29,565
Wait. Stupnitsky wants back in.

1293
01:43:35,774 --> 01:43:36,741
What?

1294
01:43:36,842 --> 01:43:40,972
Look, I've had some time
to think about what you said.

1295
01:43:42,848 --> 01:43:44,338
I want back in.

1296
01:43:45,317 --> 01:43:49,185
- Why now?
- Because I have nothing else.

1297
01:43:51,056 --> 01:43:54,253
All right, look, Ben. I'm not gonna lie to you.
You're good, you're very, very good.

1298
01:43:54,359 --> 01:43:58,523
But you did exactly what I told you not to.
You got emotional and then you got stupid.

1299
01:43:58,630 --> 01:44:02,327
Now you tell me why in the world
I'd ever get back in business with you.

1300
01:44:02,434 --> 01:44:06,894
Look, I know I should never have
disrespected you, all right? I know that.

